    <h2> Budgeting for January </h2>
    <p>It is January. I wish you a happy new year! I hope that you have enjoyed yourself in December, and that you have succeeded in finding and giving meaningful presents. How was it for you to reflect on your year? Have you succeeded in the preliminary definition of objectives for January?</p>
    <h3>Properties of January</h3>
        <p>January is the month of new objectives. Or, the way most people would state it, “new beginnings”. With last year’s end-of-year festivities, you have celebrated the end of something, and in January something new is started.</p>
        <p>What is your New Year’s Resolution? (If you would like to read a recommendation on how to define a good New Year’s Resolution, <a>click here</a>.) I hope that it is inclusive of plenty of beautiful philosophy. The New Year’s Resolution is a central theme in the month of January.</p>
        <p>The New Year’s Resolution is a combination of philosophy and objectives. Philosophy about where you stand at the beginning of the new year, where you have been and where you desire to be. You might better know what works for you and what does not work. Objectives could find themselves in the context of health and fitness, objectives of education, wealth-related objectives: the list of types is endless. May you find confidence in your New Year’s Resolution. That and the fact that the winter season has started, are the main properties of January.</p>
<h3>Financial Principles of January</h3>
<p>December was about the focus on togetherness. In terms of administration, therefore, it is not rare to be a little backlogged in January. But given that we want to start off the new year fresh and clean, it is important to close off last year’s administration and start a brand new one, both in the month of January. (And not sooner or later than the month of January.)</p>
        <p>Your administrative responsibilities for the month are likely related to national policies of taxation. It is best to keep your administration in a formatting that is compatible with the way in which your administration is called upon by the government.</p>
        <p>After all duties in the context of last year are finished, last year’s administration may be archived and it is time to start a new one. Are there lessons of your previous administration that you would like to implement in your new administration? (If you would like to receive recommendations on how to organize your administration, <a>click here</a>)</p>
